5:
Man, did you ever pick the wrong
ship to attack. Talk about bad luck.
8:
S-screw you! Do you really think
we're gonna let ourselves get
caught here?
15:
If we don't do something about this,
we'll be at the bottom of the sea
before long!
17:
What's that? It smells like something
here needs fixing!
20:
Yep, my nose is rarely wrong—that is
one royally messed up engine
crying out for someone to fix it!
23:
Oy, who the hell are you? Get away,
we can't have amateurs tinkering
with that!
26:
AMATEUR? Buddy, you're dealing
with a full-blown professional here.
31:
I'm Elegia, the handiest
repairwoman you ever did meet! I'll
fix anything up, good as new!
36:
You're the only reason we made it
out alive. I don't know how to thank
you...
39:
No biggie. It was also in my best
interests not to drown, after all!
42:
Anyway, if you need maintenance
done on that baby, you know who to
call—Elegia's Repair Service, there
for your every need! Hehe.
46:
Elegia, is it? We are also in your debt.
Thank you for your aid.
50:
Ahaha, like I said, it's really no biggie.
Plus, you guys helped beat up those
pirates! You're pretty tough
yourselves.
55:
Kicking pirate butt is one thing; fixing
up a ship like that is another. Not
just anyone can do that all on their
own.
59:
Hehe. I'm a solo contractor, that's
what I do! "All mechanics can attest,
Elegia IS the best!" That's my slogan.
64:
And you too, can avail yourselves of
my services! If ever you have a
product that needs fixing... call...
Elegia's...
70:
Um, Elegia?
Wait... Did she fall asleep?!
75: H-huh? Oh crap, sorry about that!
80:
I've been pulling a lot of all-nighters
recently. About to hit my limit... by
the looks... of it...
84:
Hold on, now! You can't just sleep
here! Let's go find you room and
board somewhere!
89:
Nah... It's okay... My house is really
close. Thanks for... everything today...
94:
I feel bad for just entering her house
like this...
98:
Can't be helped. She wasn't going to
get home on her own, that's for sure.
102:
This really is the studio of a
mechanic—perhaps I should have
expected that much, but the sheer
number of contraptions is incredible.
107:
No kidding. I can't help but get a
little excited seeing a place like this!
112:
Speaking of repairs, what do you
think about getting that
thingamabob fixed? It's been acting
up.
116:
You mean our oven? Yeah, it has
been on its last legs recently.
118: But... can we really ask her to do that?
124:
Many of the machines we have in
Starview Village make use of
advanced technology from other
worlds. Even she may struggle to—
134:
Oh, sorry, were we being too loud?
We'll get out of your hair now, get
some rest!
140: Not before you tell me more, I won't!
148:
Is this "oven" thing powered by
elements? Or is it electrothermal?
You know what, doesn't matter, once
I see it—
152:
H-hold on, now! Let's relax, okay?
Don't you need to sleep?
157:
Pfft, don't you worry about that. A
riveting talk about repairing
machines is all I need to wake right
up!
160:
Plus, I'd really hate to let a job get
away from me—especially one
staring me in the eyes like this!
168:
It's my goal to be the best
repairperson there ever was!
173:
To do that, I need to practice. I can't
let valuable repair experience slip
me by!
176:
Especially if it concerns technology
from these "other worlds" of yours!
I'd be an idiot to pass that up!
187:
Please, I'm begging you, tell me
more! I won't even charge you
anything!
195:
What?! But, I'll keep it all a secret, I
swear!
198:
No, not that part. I meant that we
absolutely cannot let you work for
free.
202:
Wh-whoa! This place is so, so, so, SO
awesome! I can't believe it!
211:
But you must promise not to utter a
word of this to anyone else. Oh, and
to get some sleep as well.
214:
Roger that! But repairing comes first,
no matter what!
218:
Great... We've got a workaholic on
our hands, huh?
